ting one. Let me read both result sections and, crucially, check whether a dispatch-fallback-activated appeared, and whether count-actions style multiplicities show anything odd.Compare how B and C block - different mechanisms expectedCompare how B and C block - different mechanisms expectedHere_apostrophe_s the first piece of unexpected gold — and it_apostrophe_s subtle. Look at the true counts before the empty ():_newline__newline_Cell B (match-fixed, lifecycle-broken): four trues, then ()._newline_Cell C (match-broken, lifecycle-fixed): five trues, then ()._newline_Cell D (both fixed): five trues, then (skill-discovery)._newline__newline_The true lines are the goal-success markers for each !() statement that ran. Both B and C seed the same number of fixture atoms in terms of probe structure — but B has lifecycle_fixed=False so it seeds 2 fixture atoms (cap + handler), and C has lifecycle_fixed=True so it seeds 3 (cap + handler + eligible-lifecycle). Then each runs dispatch + the collapse-read._newline_Let me count precisely. B fixture = 2 atoms, C fixture = 3 atoms. Plus dispatch (1) plus the collapse read (1). So B should show 2+1 = 3 trues before the read result, C should show 3+1 = 4. But I_apostrophe_m seeing 4 for B and 5 for C. That_apostrophe_s one extra true in each. That extra is the lib_import line at the top — it also emits a goal result. So: B = import(1) + 2 seeds + dispatch(1) = 4 trues, then (). C = import(1) + 3 seeds + dispatch(1) = 5 trues, then (). That accounts cleanly. Good — no anomaly there, the counts are exactly right and they confirm the fixture sizes differ as designed._newline_But that_apostrophe_s not the gold. The gold is what_apostrophe_s missing: neither B nor C shows a dispatch-fallback-activated in the read. The read only queries capability-invoked, which is empty in both. So from this probe alone, I cannot tell whether B blocked at the lifecycle filter (entered pipeline, dropped) or whether it fell back the same way C did (never