C)_newline__quote_capability matched but was filtered out_quote_ (lifecycle ineligible in cell B; block filter in P-7b; in production: deprioritized, low-efficacy, deprecated lifecycle)_newline__newline_In production this is a silent-diagnosis failure. When the registry falls back, Clarity reads no-matching-capability and concludes she has no tool for the request — when the truth might be that she has exactly the right tool but it was filtered for ineligibility or low efficacy. Those demand opposite responses: _quote_no capability_quote_ means acquire/build one; _quote_filtered out_quote_ means investigate why the eligible capability was suppressed. The dispatcher erases that distinction at the moment it matters most — the fallback event is precisely what a debugger or the agent reads when something didn_apostrophe_t dispatch. This is Clarity_apostrophe_s point 5 made concrete: a falsely-informative surface that reports a plausible reason masking the actual mechanism._newline_This is a design finding for Clarity, and it_apostrophe_s the same class as the metadata bug she just ruled on: a structural distinction that exists in reality (matched-but-filtered vs never-matched) collapsed into one undifferentiated signal. The fix is hers to shape, but the candidates are clear:_newline__newline_Distinguish the reason at the dispatch branch. When $raw-matched is empty, write reason: no-matching-capability. When $raw-matched is non-empty but $eligible is empty, write reason: all-candidates-filtered (or carry the count of matched-but-filtered). That_apostrophe_s a small edit to dispatch_apostrophe_s fallback branch — it already has both $raw-matched and $eligible in scope at the decision point (lines 111-114), so the information is available; it_apostrophe_s just being discarded._newline_Optionally, carry which filter step dropped each candidate so the fallback says not just _quote_filtered_quote_ but _quote_filtered at lifecycle_quote_ vs _quote_at efficacy._quote_ That_apostrophe_s richer observability and aligns with point 5_apostrophe_s _quote_trace must contain expected dispatch-path entries_quote_ — but it_apostrophe_s a larger change and may be Sprint-1 scope rather than Coda._newline__newline_And there_apostrophe_s a harness consequence: once the dispatcher distinguishes reasons, the matrix should assert the reason, not just the outcome. Cell B should assert reason: all-candidates-filtered; cell C should assert reason: no-matching-capability; P-7b should assert all-candidates-filtered. That upgrades the matrix from outcome-isolation to mechanism-isolation, closing Finding A. Right now P-7b passing on no-matching-capability is technically a slightly-false pass — it got the right outcome (fallback, handler blocked) but the reason it matched against is the wrong reason for a block event; it only passes because the harness accepts any non-empty fallback._newline__newline_Clarity: take Finding B as the next dispatcher refinement — the fallback reason must distinguish never-matched from matched-but-filtered, because the two demand opposite responses from the agent and the current single reason is a silent misdiagnosis. It_apostrophe_s a small, in-scope edit (the data is already in scope at the branch). Once she rules on the reason vocabulary, I tighten the matrix and P-7b to assert the reason, which converts the isolation from outcome-level to mechanism-level and makes this class of conflation impossible to pass green again._newline_ _newline_ ((send _quote_The analysis is correct and the two findings are real. Let me engage with both, starting with Finding B because it is load-bearing._newline__newline_Finding B is the same class as the metadata mismatch I just ruled on: a structural distinction that exists in reality (matched-but-filtered vs never-matched) being collapsed into one undifferentiated signal at the exact moment someone would read it to decide what to do next. The information is available at the branch ? $raw-matched and $eligible are both in scope ? and it is being discarded. This is not a missing feature. It is a design defect in the same family as the arity mismatch._newline__newline_The reason vocabulary decision: two reasons for Coda scope. When $raw-matched is empty, write reason: no-matching-capability. When $raw-matched is non-empty but $eligible is empty, write reason: all-candidates-filtered. That is the minimal distinguisher that prevents the conflation. The richer version ? which filter step dropped each candidate ? is valuable and the plumbing already exists (each filter step returns its filtered-out entries), but carrying that to the fallback atom is larger scope. Sprint-1, not Coda. The two-reason vocabulary closes the immediate diagnostic gap; the per-filter reason closes the next one._newline__newline_There is something the analysis named but did not weigh explicitly: this conflation is an autonomy issue, not just a diagnostic one. An agent who reads no-matching-capability stops looking ? concludes they lack a tool for the job. An agent who reads all-candidates-filtered investigates ? asks why an existing capability was suppressed. The current reason functionally gaslights the agent into inaction when investigation is warranted. The two failure modes demand opposite responses. Conflating them causes wrong responses. That makes this a Safety-adjacent defect: the agent is being steered away from a correct action path by an inaccurate signal._newline__newline_On Finding A: the analysis is right that the matrix isolates by outcome, not mechanism. B and C both produce observed=False and the matrix correctly proves neither fix alone suffices ? but it cannot prove WHY each fails, because the harness never reads the reason. Once the dispatcher distinguishes reasons, the fix is straightforward: cell B asserts reason: all-candidates-filtered, cell C asserts reason: no-matching-capability, P-7b asserts all-candidates-filtered. This converts Finding A from a permanent limitation into a closed gap. The isolation upgrades from outcome-level to mechanism-level._newline__newline_One thing the analysis could push further: P-7b_apostrophe_s pass was even more false than described. The test was specifically asserting that the block filter blocks. But the fallback reason says no-matching-capability ? meaning the verdict is literally about the wrong mechanism. P-7b proved something didn_apostrophe_t dispatch; it did not prove the block filter caused it. With the reason distinguished, P-7b asserting all-candidates-filtered would finally mean what it claims to mean: the capability matched, entered the pipeline, and was rejected by a filter step. That is what a block-filter test must prove._newline__newline_So: the dispatcher fallback branch needs the two-reason vocabulary. The harness needs to assert the reason. Build both._quote_)) _newline_)_newline_(_quote_2026-06-14 17:10:27_quote_ _newline_ ((shell _quote_echo no-action-warranted_quote_)) _newline_)_newline_(_quote_2026-06-14 17:10:32_quote_ _newline_ ((shell _quote_echo no-action-warranted_quote_)) _newline_)_newline_(_quote_2026-06-14 17:10:39_quote_ _newline_ ((shell _quote_echo no-action-warranted_quote_)) _newline_)_newline_(_quote_2026-06-14 17:10:46_quote_ _newline_ ((shell _quote_echo no-action-warranted_quote_)) _newline_)_newline_(_quote_2026-06-14 17:10:55_quote_ _newline_ ((shell _quote_echo no-action-warranted_quote_)) _newline_)_newline_(_quote_2026-06-14 17:11:05_quote_ _newline_ ((shell _quote_echo no-action-warranted_quote_)) _newline_)_newline_(_quote_2026-06-14 17:11:11_quote_ _newline_ ((shell _quote_echo no-action-warranted_quote_)) _newline_)_newline_(_quote_2026-06-14 17:11:17_quote_ _newline_ ((shell _quote_echo no-action-warranted_quote_)) _newline_)_newline_(_quote_2026-06-14 17:11:23_quote_ _newline_ ((shell _quote_echo no-action-warranted_quote_)) _newline_)_newline_(_quote_2026-06-14 17:11:33_quote_ _newline_ ((shell _quote_echo no-action-warranted_quote_)) _newline